---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { buildAuthorSchema, buildBreadcrumbs } from "../components/seo/SchemaBuilder";

const meta = {
  title:      "About Johan van der Merwe – Starburst Slots ZA",
  description: "Johan van der Merwe is a South African casino games reviewer specialising in NetEnt slots. Learn about his methodology and experience testing online slots.",
  noindex:    false,
  ogImage:    "/images/og/starburst-about.webp",
  ogImageAlt: "Johan van der Merwe casino games reviewer South Africa",
};

const schema = [
  buildAuthorSchema(),
  buildBreadcrumbs([
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "About", path: "/about/" },
  ]),
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  ogImage={meta.ogImage}
  ogImageAlt={meta.ogImageAlt}
  noindex={meta.noindex}
  schema={schema}
  ogType="article"
>
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
      <div class="container" style="padding-block: 0.875rem;">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-dim);">
          <a href="/" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none;">Home</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true" style="margin-inline: 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5;">›</span>
          <span style="color: var(--color-text);">About</span>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container section">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin-inline: auto;">

      <!-- Author header -->
      <div
        style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--spacing-xl); flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);"
        itemscope
        itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/author.webp"
          width="120"
          height="120"
          alt="Johan van der Merwe"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
          itemprop="image"
          style="border-radius: 50%; shrink: 0;"
          class="rounded-full"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm); color: var(--color-text);" itemprop="name">
            Johan van der Merwe
          </h1>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1rem;" itemprop="jobTitle">
            Casino Games Reviewer — South Africa
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text);">
          About this site
        </h2>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8;">
          <p>
            I started reviewing online casino games in 2018, mostly because the South African player experience was getting ignored by the big international review sites. They'd write about UK casinos, maybe throw in some Euros, and act like the ZAR didn't exist. It got old fast.
          </p>
          <p>
            This site focuses entirely on Starburst — NetEnt's long-running low-volatility slot that's still somehow everywhere in 2026. I cover how the game actually works, what the RTP means in practice, and which ZAR casinos are worth playing it at. Everything I write comes from playing the game myself, on real devices, at real stakes.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've tested over 40 NetEnt titles since 2018. Starburst gets a disproportionate amount of my attention because it's the most commonly promoted slot for South African players, and the information out there about it ranges from thin to misleading. I'd rather write one site that gets it right than copy what everyone else is saying.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Methodology -->
      <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text);">
          How I test casinos
        </h2>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8;">
          <p>
            <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">Licence first.</strong> I check every recommended casino against the <a href="https://www.wcgb.org.za/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Western Cape Gambling Board</a> or an equivalent authority (MGA, UKGC, Curaçao eGaming). If the licence isn't verifiable, the casino doesn't appear on this site.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">Real deposits, real withdrawals.</strong> I make ZAR deposits using methods South African players actually have — EFT, Ozow, Visa. I play Starburst at stakes I'd consider realistic (usually R18–R36 per spin, which mirrors what a R200 session looks like). Then I request a withdrawal. The speed and friction of that process matters more than any headline bonus number.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">Minimum 200 spins before conclusions.</strong> I don't write about game feel after 20 spins. Low-volatility slots need room to show their variance. I run at least 200 spins in demo before real money, and at least 100 spins with real stakes. Re-spin chains need to appear naturally to assess frequency.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">Device testing.</strong> Desktop (Chrome/Firefox), mid-range Android (Samsung Galaxy A series), iPhone 12 and newer. If the mobile experience degrades — slower loads, misaligned buttons, audio cutting out — I note it. Most players in South Africa are on mobile, often on LTE, not fibre.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">Player complaints.</strong> I check <a href="https://www.askgamblers.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">AskGamblers</a> and <a href="https://www.trustpilot.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Trustpilot</a> for each casino before recommending it. A couple of complaints is normal at any large operator. A pattern of unresolved withdrawal denials after wins is not.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Affiliate disclosure -->
      <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text);">
          Affiliate disclosure
        </h2>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8;">
          <p>
            Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you register at a casino through one and make a deposit, I earn a commission. This is how the site stays free to run.
          </p>
          <p>
            It doesn't change what I write. Casinos I've had bad experiences with — slow payouts, hidden wagering terms, unresponsive support — don't appear here regardless of what they'd pay. The ones I recommend are ones I've tested myself and would send a friend to. That's the only standard I apply.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- E-E-A-T signals -->
      <section style="padding-top: var(--spacing-xl); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
      <div style="background: var(--color-bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--spacing-xl);">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md); color: var(--color-text);">
          Quick facts
        </h2>
        <ul style="list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--spacing-sm); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 0.875rem;">
          <li>Reviewing SA online casino games since 2018</li>
          <li>40+ NetEnt titles tested at real-money stakes</li>
          <li>Starburst tested on Android, iOS, and desktop — multiple device generations</li>
          <li>RTP figures sourced from official <a href="https://www.netent.com/en/game/starburst/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">NetEnt documentation</a> and verified in-game paytables</li>
          <li>Casino licence status checked against <a href="https://www.wcgb.org.za/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">WCGB</a>, MGA, and UKGC registers</li>
          <li>No paid placements — editorial decisions are mine alone</li>
          <li>Responsible gambling resources: <a href="https://www.responsiblegambling.org.za/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-primary);">NRGP (0800 006 008)</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      </section>

    </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
